About

Rocket Factory Augsburg hosts this event as a launch service provider for small satellites into Low Earth Orbits at unrivalled prices starting end of 2022.

 

Now that we have been able to demonstrate the full functionality of our staged combustion engine with a successful 8-second test, we would like to take this as an opportunity to put our successes, our technology and new space in general into a broader context: The commercialization of Space Transportation in Europe.

 

In April of this year, the EU published its space program. In addition to the economic benefits of data and services, the program focuses on two things in particular: the EU’s security and autonomy in space and its important role as a leading player in the space economy. The panel discussion will share perspectives with selected participants on where European space is heading and what role inexpensive and efficient commercial launchers can play in this.

 

 

Join us in this online event with insights from our management, a panel discussion with experts and a live Q&A!

Speakers

Stefan Brieschenk

Chief Operating Officer - Rocket Factory Augsburg

Stefan has an international career in the industry and previously held positions at Rocket Lab USA and MT Aerospace in Germany. He has a strong technical background and his current focus is dedicated to utilizing industrial solutions to allow for order-of-magnitude cost-reductions in the sector.

Jörn Spurmann

Chief Commercial Officer - Rocket Factory Augsburg

As Rocket Factory’s Co-founder he operationalized the company mid of 2018. Mr. Spurmann has a proven track record as head of sales, program and business unit manager in the space domain. Throughout his senior leadership roles he has gained excellent knowledge of the institutional and commercial space business.

Speakers

Stefan Brieschenk

Chief Operating Officer - Rocket Factory Augsburg

Stefan has an international career in the industry and previously held positions at Rocket Lab USA and MT Aerospace in Germany. He has a strong technical background and his current focus is dedicated to utilizing industrial solutions to allow for order-of-magnitude cost-reductions in the sector.

Jörn Spurmann

Chief Commercial Officer - Rocket Factory Augsburg

As Rocket Factory’s first employee he operationalized the company mid of 2018. Mr. Spurmann has a proven track record as head of sales, program and business unit manager in the space domain. Throughout his senior leadership roles he has gained excellent knowledge of the institutional and commercial space business.

Panelists

Rüdeger Albat

Mr. Albat is ESA‘s head of Ariane 5 and of Preparation of Future Space Transporation.  He is an aerospace engineer anchored in space transportation since the early days of Ariane. He  has actively participated in more than 50 Ariane launches, from Ariane 1 to Ariane 5, in many different operational roles. 

Mr. Albat has witnessed the ramp-up of the European space transportation sector, from early commercial debuts to the wide fields of the current emerging opportunities for new space eco-systems.

Thomas Jarzombek

Commissioner for Digital Industry and Start-ups at the Ministry of Economic Affairs. He is also the German Aerospace Policy Coordinator for the Federal Government. Mr. Jarzombek is in charge of coordinating and bringing together the Federal Government’s efforts to improve Germany’s aerospace sector’s international competitiveness in research and development.

Jeanne Medvedeva

Jeanne is the Vice President of Launch Services at Exolaunch GmbH, a leading Germany-based provider of launch, in-space logistics, deployment and integration services for small satellites. Jeanne has worked with multiple launch vehicles and rideshare missions to arrange successful launches of over 230 small satellites (as of today) for the New Space actors.

Frank Thelen

Mr. Thelen is a serial entrepreneur, tech investor, and TV personality from Germany. As founder, he concentrates on early-stage investments like Lilium Aviation, Endurosat, Smartlane, Roboco, Xentral, among others. He’s also the author of two best-selling publications, “Startup-DNA” and “10xDNA.

Frank Thelen

Confirmed

Mr. Thelen is a serial entrepreneur, tech investor, and TV personality from Europe. He concentrates on seed investments like Lilium Aviation, Wunderlist, Xentral, and YFood as the Founder and CEO of Freigeist Capital. He’s also the author of two best-selling publications, “Startup-DNA” and “10xDNA.”

Rob Meyerson

Invited

Founder and CEO of Delalune Space, a management consulting firm that provides advisory services to clients in the aerospace, mobility, technology, and finance sectors. He was the previous president of Blue Origin, a spaceflight business dedicated to lowering the cost of spaceflight and assisting in the exploration of the solar system. He formerly worked at Kistler Aerospace as a senior manager.
